From: Kyle Camera Local Quirk <kyle@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] media: i2c: ov08x40: avoid broken binned modes on IPU7

The 1928-wide binned modes produce black frames on this IPU7/OV08X40
laptop, while full sensor modes produce valid frames. Keep the mode
tables in place, but stop advertising the binned modes through the
mode filter so libcamera's simple pipeline selects a full sensor mode
and scales from there.
---
 drivers/media/i2c/ov08x40.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/ov08x40.c b/drivers/media/i2c/ov08x40.c
index 31062eedbd71..1bc3b5b3a53a 100644
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/ov08x40.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/ov08x40.c
@@ -1761,6 +1761,14 @@ static bool filter_by_mipi_lanes(const void *array, size_t index,
 	const struct ov08x40_mode *mode = array;
 	const struct ov08x40 *ov08x = context;
 
+	/*
+	 * The binned 1928-wide modes trigger IPU7 stream errors and black
+	 * frames on this platform. Force clients through the full sensor mode
+	 * until the bad binned register set is fixed upstream.
+	 */
+	if (mode->width == 1928)
+		return false;
+
 	return mode->lanes == ov08x->mipi_lanes;
 }
 
